<br>
Mages are an extremely efficient class. We may not be the best at efficiency for solo exp (Necros hold that category), but when it comes to groups, and taking down big mobs, we are the best.<br>
<br>
1) Pets. With the pet resist changes, and the new resist system, I find all my pets to be useful on AE mobs (Dragons mainly). My guild's first Telk takedown, I used an Air pet and with my FR at around 175 my pet took almost no damage from his AE. A pet that is in there is doing DPS and that's the key.<br>
<br>
During regular exp groups, having the right pet is the same or better than having another melee. My catch phrase is &quot;More DPS than you can shake a stick at&quot; and it's true.<br>
<br>
2) Nukes. We may not be packed with nukes, but we have them and everytime we use one it boosts our overall DPS. With our focus items we get a substantial increase and as the AAs flow in and we invest in certain skills it only gets better.<br>
<br>
We may not always be able to Nuke on Big Mobs, but when we can it's even more of a boon. Having a manaless nuke helps out in this department, when you are relegated to pumping out Mod Rods, but even if we don't nuke, our pet is doing our damage for us so it's not a big deal.<br>
<br>
3) Damage Shield. I'd say the most important ability we have other than our pets. Slap a DS on a tank and a mob is doing Damage to himself for us. I've known add mobs in an exp group to take it's HPs down to half before we get around to killing it because of the DS I have provided.<br>
<br>
Those 3 things alone would make us a force to be reckoned with, but add in all of our other abilities... Focus items, Mod rods, Mala/Malosini, etc... And we're probably right in there under &quot;Needed for flawless raiding&quot;. Make no mistake about it, if you are a good Mage, then you make things happen no matter how you contribute. <p><center><img border="0" src="http://www.nu-frontier.com/design/iggysig1.jpg" width="400" height="150"><br>"I laugh in the face of danger, and then I hide until it goes away."  - Xander Harris (Buffy the Vampire Slayer)</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umantria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mantria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 4:22:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.DaveShirley.org/neil/rock_beast_03_t%5B1%5D.gif height=150 width=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Opinions in the end game: Vex Thal</span><hr size=1> nice post...........!<br>
