Question concerning pets and VT in general.  I've noticed in some places pets can be kinda uhm hazardous being stuff likes to agro threw walls.  This is especially the case when people use their horses in VT.  When doing bloods we've had two wipe-outs with pets up. no wipeouts without pets.  People will say sure that's what pethold is for. No that's NOT what its for. once a pet is told to engage it no longer is in the 'pethold' status but full attack mode. ie agro mode. thus generates agro like anyone else.   How have you gotta around this, or more to the point how do you control this agro?  This is the main reason the mages in my guild, and all the pet classes actually don't use pets for the yardtrash grind. bosses yeah we do cept for the first glob of snot.  The gflux sends pets through roof thus generating more agro from there and mobs warpin down.(something verant has still to get fixed)<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway I am asking because well I've simply not found a way to control agro once pet is engaged.<br>
