<br>
The guild I currently participate with makes sure everyone is a fine oil machine.  Sometimes we know it's a gamble for a CR but that doesn't stop us.  For the most part, we are always prepared for a high end encounter.<br>
<br>
CotH - been out since Kunark and lvl 55.  Always essential to have mages grouped with monks.  CotH from the zonelines, group with a druid/necro/wiz and summon em to camp.  Nothing has changed with this....<br>
<br>
Loose ends - Focus Items/Coldstones - With the loot enhancements in VT, you will see these requests less common.  Coldstones?  There are a ton of high end items that support these needs, sure summon if people need but if you are in a high end guild, most toons should be equipped with an item with truesight etc....  If not, you are recruiting a lot of players with no gear or skipping other content....<br>
<br>
Mala/Malo - More kunark skillz, sure good to help the shaman, but if you have shaman raiding that can only focus on one task, which is usually slowing if not buffing then maybe you better post on a shaman board of what skills they are capable of.  Again, I guess I am spoiled.  The guild I participate with can raid with anywhere from 2-6 shaman.  When it's 2, things don't slow down.  They debuff, slow, torpor, buff the killed.  Again, the AA skill of Cann5 makes them a powerful class.  Because while they have done the tasks mentioned above, they are also torporing anywhere from 1-4 mages to crank out rods.<br>
<br>
I also think the comments about nuking was funny with your wizards.  So you recruit wizards who don't know how to manage their aggro?  Nukes are good but considered secondary.  Name of the game is DPS especially if you are fighting named in VT that could take 25-45 mins to kill with other pops respawning in 45 mins or less from clearing to it.  Wizards have the better nukes, let them burn the mob down.  The more mana you can feed them, the more they can burn.<br>
<br>
Damage shields - DS'ing your group?  How about your tanks that are taking damage?  Dagger off creator makes it helpful.  Also stock your bards up with lava gems from Sarnak staffs from VP.  Again, this stuff has been out since Kunark....<br>
<br>
Pets - Sure it's dps, but like you say, the one time it decides to warp through a wall and bring back friends or even die and summon you to death to stop the mana production will make the raid more interesting.  I never use my pet, sure I have pet hold but we have enough melee/rogue/wiz to take down mobs so he isn't needed.  It also allows me to hide if things go bad in some instances.  Once you send pet you have put yourself on the hatelist.<br>
<br>
Mod Rods - very powerful.  Almost too powerful and is becoming a taboo for VI.  Shaman are your pals for mod rod production.  Screw SoA's, the only time your rune items become useful is if shaman are dead or you raid without shaman .  AA skills are a plus.  Sure it makes you cast faster, doesn't necessarily mean you are a good rodder.  Mages go a step further with mod rods.  Be able to act on command.  Place rods where clerics request them if a camp is moved in the middle of combat due to rampage aggro.  Personally I will use my QS2, casting mastery, spell haste, 3900 mana pool with 4600 hp and make any encounter a success.  Any mage with a shaman will do just as good even without the skills.  Another key to mod rodding is keeping track of rods and swapping.  Don't let em poof.  While prepping for a boss, you can easily have a stack of 100+ rods ready to go.  You could even have more depending on the boss you are going after such as Aten or Seru.  Want rods more fancy, just get a torpor and start clicking off your stack to make nice carpets for your clerics once the fight starts for easy clickage to obtain em.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, the post was titled &quot;Opinions in the end game: Vex Thal&quot;  but like I commented earlier, a lot of the skills have been around since Kunark.  Are you telling me you have mages raid the high end game that are not aware of their skills?  How do you get to lvl 60 and not know what you are capable of - ebay, playerauctions?  If this was a post for young mages for expectations of the high end game then maybe a valid post.  If you are raiding VT, you should already know this.  And thats what makes this game what it is, peeps can say oh I have a SoA or item x, but if you don't know how to use what you have, it does no good for your guild.  Knowledge is real power for the mage....<br>
<br>
Sage Mada Amstier<br>
Archmage of the Rathe<br>
Blood of the Spider<br>
